{"data":{"actions":[{"callId":"chatcmpl-tool-b144253346323b1a","input":{"filename":"data_catalog_steward_action_report.md","title":"Data Catalog Steward Prioritized Action Report","markdown":"# Data Catalog Steward Prioritized Action Report\n\n**Scope:** Summary of the three highest‑scoring operational records for the Data Catalog Steward (ID 38) and recommended next steps.\n\n---\n\n## 1. Immediate Action – Record **38‑A** (Urgent)\n- **Title:** Data catalog steward priority case\n- **Owner:** Data Governance (verified)\n- **Impact:** 54,046 pts – highest‑impact open item.\n- **Risk Score:** 9 (high)\n- **Opportunity Score:** 7\n- **Key Issues:**\n  - Potential gaps in dataset ownership documentation.\n  - Freshness SLAs not verified for several critical datasets.\n  - PII classification missing for at least two high‑volume tables.\n\n### Recommended Steps (within 2 days)\n1. **Run ownership audit** – extract current catalog (e.g., via the metadata repository) and cross‑check against the governance registry. Flag any dataset lacking an owner.\n2. **Validate freshness SLAs** – query the data quality logs for the last 30 days; mark any dataset whose ingestion lag exceeds the defined SLA.\n3. **PII scan** – invoke the PII detection pipeline on the flagged tables; update the catalog with classifications (PII / non‑PII).\n4. **Document findings** – add a brief note to each affected record in the catalog and notify the Data Governance team through the standard ticketing channel.\n\n**Assumptions:** Access to the metadata store and PII scanner is functional; no pending outages.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Resolve Blocked Work – Record **38‑C** (Blocked)\n- **Title:** Data catalog steward blocked follow‑up\n- **Owner:** Data Governance\n- **Impact:** 26,018 pts\n- **Risk Score:** 7 (moderate‑high)\n- **Status:** Blocked – requires cross‑functional coordination.\n\n### Recommended Steps (within 5 days)\n1. **Identify dependency** – confirm which external team (e.g., Data Engineering or Legal) holds the required input.\n2. **Schedule a joint sync** – propose a 30‑minute meeting with stakeholders; include a clear agenda (release of missing metadata, legal review of PII handling).\n3. **Escalation path** – if no response within 48 h, raise a priority escalation ticket to the Data Governance lead.\n4. **Record outcome** – update the record status to *in_progress* once the dependency is resolved.\n\n**Assumptions:** Stakeholder contact information is up‑to‑date in the internal directory.\n\n---\n\n## 3. Routine Maintenance – Record **38‑B** (In Review)\n- **Title:** Data catalog steward routine queue item\n- **Owner:** Data Governance\n- **Impact:** 13,294 pts\n- **Risk Score:** 3 (low)\n- **Status:** In review.\n\n### Recommended Steps (within 10 days)\n1. **Review existing documentation** – verify that owners, freshness SLAs, and PII flags are present for the listed datasets.\n2. **Close the loop** – if everything is current, mark the record *completed* and archive it.\n3. **Add to backlog** – if minor gaps are found, create a low‑priority ticket for later iteration.\n\n**Assumptions:** No urgent regulatory deadlines for these datasets.\n\n---\n\n## Overall Prioritization\n| Priority | Record ID | Action Horizon |\n|----------|-----------|-----------------|\n| **High** | 38‑A | ≤ 2 days |\n| **Medium** | 38‑C | ≤ 5 days (dependency resolution) |\n| **Low** | 38‑B | ≤ 10 days |\n\n### Next Immediate Action\nExecute step 1 of Record 38‑A (ownership audit) and open a tracking ticket titled *\"Urgent Data Catalog Cleanup – 38‑A\"*.\n\n*Report generated based on dossier load and record analysis (3 records, total risk = 19, opportunity = 10.9). All recommendations assume normal system access and no outstanding outages.*\n"},"kind":"tool-call","toolName":"write_report"}],"sequence":0,"stepIndex":3,"turnId":"turn_0"},"type":"actions.requested","meta":{"at":"2026-06-18T15:24:01.205Z"}}
